Education. Members include representatives of educational institutions and agencies, professional employee
organizations and unions, unified military commands, school administrators, parents of DoDDS students, and one
DoDDS student. The Director, DoDDS, serves as the Executive Secretary of the Council. The purpose of the Council is
to advise the Secretary of Defense and the DoDDS Director about effective educational programs and practices that
should be considered by DoDDS and to perform other tasks as may be required by the Secretary of Defense. The agenda includes
discussions about observations made by teams of ACDE members who visited DoDDS schools prior to the full Council meeting,
the National Education Goals, academic achievement encouragement, multicultural/multiracial diversity and
awareness, education of children with disabilities, communications throughout the system, increased parental
involvement, drawdown planning, educational technologies, and responses to the recommendations made by the Council
during its April 1994 meeting.




