The NASD requests that the Commission find good cause, pursuant to section 19(b)(2) of the Act, for approving the proposed
rule change prior to the 30th day after its publication in the 

Federal Register 

to avoid any interruption of the Service. The current authorization for the Service extends through October 3, 1994.
Hence it is imperative that the Commission approve the instant filing on or before that date. Otherwise, the NASD will
be required to suspend operation of the Service pending Commission action on the proposed extension.



The NASD believes that accelerated approval is appropriate to ensure continuity in the Service's operation pending
