Responsibilities of Scholarship Recipients.

 In order to receive the funds authorized by a scholarship award, recipients must submit Scholarship Payment Voucher
(Form S3) together with a tuition statement from the program sponsor, and a transportation fare receipt (or statement
of the driving mileage to and from the recipient's home to the site of the educational program). Recipients also must
submit to the Institute a certificate of attendance at the program and an evaluation of the educational program they
attended. A copy of the evaluation also must be sent to the Chief Justice of their State. 
A State or a local jurisdiction may impose additional requirements on scholarship recipients that are consistent
