with national import should describe how they will make their data available for secondary analysis after the grant
period. (See section X.W.) 


The curricula and other products developed by education and training projects should be designed for use outside
the classroom so that they may be used again by original participants and others in the course of their duties. 


Applicants must provide for submitting a final draft of the final grant product(s) to the Institute for review and
approval at least 30 days before the product(s) are submitted for publication or reproduction. No grant funds may
be obligated for publication or reproduction of a final grant product without the written approval of the Institute.




